Quote:  ... the Snapper (Pagrus unicolor). This name, by which it is best known, is adopted from Australia, its Maori name Tamure being seldom used by Europeans. ... The Snapper is not reputed to occur south of the Kaikoura Peninsula, the fish which usually goes by that name in the Dunedin market being the Tarakihi.
